docs.abstract: The panel has been involved with impeachment proceedings against three presidents. On Wednesday, Donald Trump will be the fourth.
docs.snippet: The panel has been involved with impeachment proceedings against three presidents. On Wednesday, Donald Trump will be the fourth.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Since its creation in 1813, the House Judiciary Committee has served as the backdrop to debates over the most contentious issues in American history, including a woman’s right to vote, immigration and civil rights. It has either held or recommended impeachment proceedings against three presidents: Andrew Johnson, Richard M. Nixon and Bill Clinton.
